<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF8DFFC7A7ADFD5FFBE1D8C0" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF8DFFC7A7ADFD5FFEF0DECB" blockId="20.[189,310,688,714]" box="[189,310,688,714]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF8DFFC7A7ADFD5FFEF0DECB" bold="true" box="[189,310,688,714]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A7ADFD5FFEF0DECB" bold="true" box="[189,310,688,714]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF8DFFC7A7ADFD0DFBD2DFE3" blockId="20.[187,1399,738,995]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Based on the description of 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF8DFFC7A6EDFD0DFCDCDEFD" author="Teruel R. &amp; Questel K." box="[509,794,738,764]" firstAuthor="Teruel" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="15 - 18" part="49" refId="ref154490" refString="Teruel R. &amp; Questel K. 2011. A new species of Charinus Simon 1892 (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Leeward Islands, Lesser Antilles. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 49: 15 - 18." title="A new species of Charinus Simon 1892 (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from the Leeward Islands, Lesser Antilles" type="journal article" year="2011">Teruel &amp; Questel (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, this species may be separated from other Caribbean and Central American 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A6C0FCE7FDFBDF23" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[464,573,776,802]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A6C0FCE7FDFBDF23" box="[464,573,776,802]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by means of the following combination of characters: median eyes, median ocular tubercle, and lateral eyes well developed; pedipalp femur with four dorsal spines and three ventral spines; pedipalp patella with three dorsal spines, large setiferous tubercle between spine I and distal margin and two ventral spines; pedipalp tarsus with two dorsal spines, distal spine twice as long as proximal spine; tibia of leg I with 22 articles, tarsus I with 39 articles; first tarsal article about three times as long as second; leg IV basitibia with three pseudo-articles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF8DFFC7A7ADFBE2FBE1D8C0" blockId="20.[189,1399,1037,1217]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A7ADFBE2FE4CD826" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Questel" authorityYear="2011" box="[189,394,1037,1063]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruneti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A7ADFBE2FE4CD826" box="[189,394,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Charinus bruneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is among the few species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A5E4FBE2FCA7D826" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[756,865,1037,1063]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A5E4FBE2FCA7D826" box="[756,865,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Caribbean and Central America with median eyes, a character present only in 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A589FBDCFCCED84C" baseAuthorityName="Quintero" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[665,776,1075,1101]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acosta">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A589FBDCFCCED84C" box="[665,776,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. acosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A406FBDCFC51D84C" authorityName="Moya-Guzman" authorityYear="2009" box="[790,919,1075,1101]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aguayoi">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A406FBDCFC51D84C" box="[790,919,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. aguayoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A4B6FBDCFBA0D84C" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[934,1126,1075,1101]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A4B6FBDCFBA0D84C" box="[934,1126,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A38EFBDCFAD3D84C" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[1182,1301,1075,1101]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miskito" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A38EFBDCFAD3D84C" box="[1182,1301,1075,1101]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. miskito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF8DFFC7A20CFBDBFAB1D84F" box="[1308,1399,1076,1102]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The average size of the five species is similar (
<tableCitation id="4A6897D8FF8DFFC7A5FDFBB6FC83D875" box="[749,837,1113,1140]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="16.[181,251,550,579]" captionTargetBox="[181,1927,606,1741]" captionTargetId="graphics-41@16.[181,1934,631,1743]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next two pages). Measurements of all Caribbean and Central American species of Charinus Simon, 1892." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5395F2EBFF89FFC3A7A5FDC9F95BDE43" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" tableUuid="5395F2EBFF89FFC3A7A5FDC9F95BDE43">Table 1</tableCitation>
), but the count of 39 articles on tarsus of leg I distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A64DFB6FFE12D89B" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Questel" authorityYear="2011" box="[349,468,1152,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruneti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A64DFB6FFE12D89B" box="[349,468,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. bruneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A50BFB6FFD4CD89B" baseAuthorityName="Quintero" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[539,650,1152,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acosta">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A50BFB6FFD4CD89B" box="[539,650,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. acosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A589FB6FFCDCD89B" authorityName="Moya-Guzman" authorityYear="2009" box="[665,794,1152,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aguayoi">
C. 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A5ABFB6EFCDCD89B" box="[699,794,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">aguayoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A443FB6FFBD3D89B" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Coulis" authorityYear="2017" box="[851,1045,1152,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinicensis">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A443FB6FFBD3D89B" box="[851,1045,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. martinicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while the count of four dorsal spines on pedipalp femur distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A59DFB48FCC3D8C1" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Questel" authorityYear="2011" box="[653,773,1190,1217]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruneti">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A59DFB48FCC3D8C1" box="[653,773,1190,1217]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. bruneti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF8DFFC7A45DFB48FC03D8C1" authority="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff, 2021" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[845,965,1190,1217]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miskito" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF8DFFC7A45DFB48FC03D8C1" box="[845,965,1190,1217]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">C. miskito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2EADC30AFF8DFFC7A4DCFB48FBE1D8C0" box="[972,1063,1191,1217]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
